<DOC><DOCNO> AP880318-0122 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-18-88 1228EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-RetailSales     03-18 0133</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Retail Sales,130</SECOND><HEAD>Government Revises Downward Retail Sales Report for February</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Retail sales rose 0.4 percent in February, aslightly smaller increase than reported a week ago, the governmentsaid Friday.   The Commerce Department said sales last month totaled aseasonally adjusted $129.12 billion, up $525 million from theJanuary sales level.   When the sales data was first released on March 11, thegovernment reported sales had risen 0.6 percent in Februaryfollowing a 0.2 percent January decline. The new data shows thatsales were essentially unchanged in January.   The changes reflect the department's annual benchmark revisionswhich update the surveys used to gather information nationwide onsales. The changes put total retail sales in 1987 at $1.511trillion, compared with an estimate of $1.506 trillion before therevisions.</TEXT></DOC>